6779208,0.02235042,0.02546949,-0.00901617,-0.00021374,-0.01041473,0.03863216,0.01351909,0.04315586,0.00522727,0.10801861,-0.03899165,0.03224613,-0.03842239,-0.01395224,-0.02625920,-0.03749347,-0.00815503,0.01846347,0.00795014,-0.05005546,-0.00834488,0.02476494,0.00304338,-0.05527487,-0.03725271,0.02437712,-0.01311519,-0.05259642,-0.05075641,-0.04238226,0.00802202,0.04077225,0.04510000,0.03634615,0.04303693,-0.03669389,0.04747301,-0.00770981,0.01945907,0.05341721,0.10147908,0.02674442]',E'Span Kind\n\nWhen a span is created, it is one of `Client`, `Server`, `Internal`, `Producer`,\nor `Consumer`. This span kind provides a hint to the tracing backend as to how\nthe trace should be assembled. According to the OpenTelemetry specification, the\nparent of a server span is often a remote client span, and the child of a client\nspan is usually a server span. Similarly, the parent of a consumer span is\nalways a producer and the child of a producer span is always a consumer. If not\nprovided, the span kind is assumed to be internal.\n\nFor more information regarding SpanKind, see\n[SpanKind](/docs/specs/otel/trace/api/#spankind).','{"source": "opentelemetry", "version": "1.0", "language": "yaml", "title": "Traces", "section_title": "traces", "url": "https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry.io/blob/main/content/en/docs/concepts/signals/traces.md", "topics": "otel,observability,tracing,traces", "categories": "devops,observability,monitoring"}');
